                   <p class="light">It’s all about being in the right place at the right time.</p>


                   <p class="light">A good fire has three key elements working together in a careful ratio:</p> 
                   <ol style="margin-bottom:10px">
                     <li>Fuel</li>
                     <li>Oxygen</li> 
                     <li>Overall temperature</li>
                   </ol>
                    <p class="light"> When you properly mix oxygen and fuel in a fire, combustion improves, raising overall temperature which – you guessed it – further improves that combustion, allowing particles to burn easily and efficiently before they have a chance to escape the fire. The smoke you see from a typical campfire? That’s wasted fuel. The CookStove doesn’t let that happen.</p>

<p class="light">Take a look inside your CookStove’s burn chamber – you’ll see multiple small jets. When the fan system is turned on, these jets inject air all throughout the fire. By distributing the airflow, we can raise temperature evenly and ensure uniform combustion throughout.
